    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Identification of Fbx2 as a NR1-NTD-Binding Partner.\"\n- Fbx2 binds the extracellular domain of NR1.\n\nFig.3: \"Fbx2 localizes to the somatodendritic region and to synaptic spines. \"\n- \"NR1 and Fbx2 partly colocalize in somatodendritic regions (Fig. 3). Furthermore, some punctate Fbx2 staining colocalized with NR1 and/or PSD95 in synaptic spines. Synaptophysin puncta were often juxtaposed to Fbx2 puncta but were rarely overlapping, consistent with a postsynaptic function for Fbx2.\". Experimental description: - Over-expressed Fbx2 is of mouse species: \"OS7 cells were transfected with pools of clones from a mouse-brain cDNA library \"\n- Species of the neurons is (traced back to PMID:11298789): \"he primary cultures of rat hippocampal or corticalneurons were prepared essentially as described (Ono et al., 1998).\"",
